	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My speculation about the use of pin 20 in particular:<br /><br />PPU pins 40 and 20 are the PPU's power and ground pins, connected to the bypass capacitor nearest the PPU. I guess taking ground close to the PPU avoids ground loops and unwanted coupling.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


