	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Sun Jul 22, 2018 12:08 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Correct Famicom AV mod</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />68 and 82 are standard <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E_series_of_preferred_numbers#E24" class="postlink">E24</a> size resistors. 75Ω isn't.<br /><br />75Ω is actually a little too big, because the voltage follower T2 has some small finite effective output impedance, and using a 75Ω resistor would generate an unmatched transmission line.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


